  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>hake fillet[s]</strong> into 4 pieces per person</p><p>Peel and grate (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> hake pieces </strong>with the <strong>grated garlic</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong> and <strong>soy sauce</strong> to a large bowl</p><p>Give it a good mix up and set aside to marinate</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1711459011069-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1711459011069-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1711459011069-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1711459011069-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1711459011069-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and your <strong>ground turmeric </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving – this is your <strong>turmeric rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1711459013392-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1711459013392-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1711459013392-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1711459013392-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1711459013392-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>cucumber</strong> in half, scrape out the inner seeds with a teaspoon and discard, then chop in to bite-sized pieces</p><p>Combine your <strong>shredded red cabbage</strong> and <strong>chopped cucumber </strong>in a large bowl</p><p>Add your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>nigella seeds</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and set aside – this is your <strong>quick-pickled red cabbage</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1711459016638-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1711459016638-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1711459016638-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1711459016638-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1711459016638-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a small bowl, then swirl through your <strong>mango chutney </strong>– this is your <strong>mango yoghurt</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1711459019331-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1711459019331-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1711459019331-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1711459019331-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1711459019331-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Strip your<strong> mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1711459023018-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1711459023018-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1711459023018-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1711459023018-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1711459023018-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cornflour</strong> to the<strong> marinated</strong> <strong>hake pieces</strong>, and give everything a good mix up so the hake pieces are fully coated in cornflour</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1711459028583-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1711459028583-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1711459028583-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1711459028583-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1711459028583-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated hake pieces</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until browned – this is your <strong>curried crispy hake</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1711459031197-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1711459031197-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1711459031197-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1711459031197-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1711459031197-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped mint </strong>and<strong> coriander</strong> to the <strong>turmeric rice</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>herby turmeric rice</strong></p><p>Serve your <strong>curried crispy hake </strong>on top of the <strong>herby turmeric rice </strong>and the <strong>quick-pickled red cabbage </strong>to the side</p><p>Dollop the <strong>mango yoghurt </strong>over everything</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
